The paper discusses the use of Artificial Intelligence tools, specifically machine learning, to improve the performance of Automated Transit Networks (ATN, previously called Personal Rapid Transit - PRT). This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the cs.AI sub-category. Additionally, the paper focuses on improving the cooperation of autonomous modules using negotiation protocols, which falls under the cs.RO sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of IoT paradigms, which could be classified under the cs.SY sub-category. The use of machine learning to improve algorithms designed by human programmers suggests that the paper could also belong to the cs.LG sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the tuning of individual behavioral policies, which could be classified under the cs.IT sub-category.
